Input.name: Mohammad-Ali Foroughi
Input.question1: Who was the prime minister of Iran in 1913?
Input.question2: How many years was Mohammad-Ali Foroughi a member of the Parliament of Iran?
Input.question3: How long after becoming Member of the Parliament of Iran did Mohammad-Ali Foroughi become Minister of Foreign Affairs?
Answer.Res1: A prime minister is a country's governing leader, and they serve terms such as 2 years or 4 years.  Therefore, the prime ministerof Iran in 1913 was Hassan Pirnia.
Answer.Res2: A member of the Parliament of Iran is a member of the lawmaking body of the government, and they serve specified terms as members.  Mohammad-Ali Foroughi was a member of the Parliament of Iran from 1909-1921.  Therefore, Mohammad-Ali Foroughi was a member of the Parliament of Iran for 12 years.
Answer.Res3: Parliament members and ministers of foreign affairs both serve terms; parliament members are responsible for the lawmaking part of the government and ministers of foreign affairs deal with international relations with other countries. Mohammad-Ali Foroughi became a member of the Parliament of Iran in 1909, and he became a Minister of Foreign Affaris in 1923.  Therefore, Mohammad-Ali Foroughi became the Minister of Foreign Affairs 14 years after becoming a Member of the Parliament of Iran.
